"title": "5918: pleasure",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5918",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>A gratifying emotion, used in Scripture to refer to both human and divine emotions. Believers are invited to take pleasure in every aspect of God's creation, while not allowing pleasure in the creation to overshadow pleasure in the Creator himself.</p>\n<h2>Divine pleasure</h2>\n<h3>That which gives God pleasure</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps147:11\">PSA 147:11</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer9:24\">JER 9:24</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps37:23\">PSA 37:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps149:4\">PSA 149:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov11:20\">PRO 11:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov12:22\">PRO 12:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt11:25-Matt11:26\">MAT 11:25–11:26</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke10:21\">LUK 10:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt12:18\">MAT 12:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa42:1\">ISA 42:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph1:5\">EPH 1:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph1:9\">EPH 1:9</a></p>\n<h3>That which does not give God pleasure</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps5:4\">PSA 5:4</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek18:23\">EZK 18:23</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps51:16\">PSA 51:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps147:10\">PSA 147:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa1:11\">ISA 1:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek18:32\">EZK 18:32</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek33:11\">EZK 33:11</a></p>\n<h2>Human pleasure</h2>\n<h3>God provides everything for the enjoyment of life</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl8:15\">ECC 8:15</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim6:17\">1TI 6:17</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Pleasure in human physical relationships</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Song4:10\">SNG 4:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Song1:2\">SNG 1:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Song2:3\">SNG 2:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Song7:6\">SNG 7:6</a></p>\n<h3>Such pleasures are not satisfying in themselves</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl2:10-Eccl2:11\">ECC 2:10–2:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl2:1-Eccl2:2\">ECC 2:1–2:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl2:24-Eccl2:25\">ECC 2:24–2:25</a></p>\n<h3>True pleasure is found in the things of God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps16:11\">PSA 16:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps37:4\">PSA 37:4</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom7:22\">ROM 7:22</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps1:2\">PSA 1:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps35:9\">PSA 35:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps43:4\">PSA 43:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps111:2\">PSA 111:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps112:1\">PSA 112:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps119:16\">PSA 119:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov10:23\">PRO 10:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov16:13\">PRO 16:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov18:2\">PRO 18:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa55:2\">ISA 55:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer6:10\">JER 6:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer15:16\">JER 15:16</a></p>\n<h3>Pleasures may also be misleading or positively sinful</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke8:14\">LUK 8:14</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus3:3\">TIT 3:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov1:22\">PRO 1:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov2:14\">PRO 2:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl7:4\">ECC 7:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa66:3\">ISA 66:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Thess2:12\">2TH 2:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim5:6\">1TI 5:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim3:4\">2TI 3:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb11:25\">HEB 11:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas4:3\">JAS 4:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet2:13-2Pet2:14\">2PE 2:13–2:14</a></p>",
